    "Body": " Sr. DevOps Engineer Cisco Systems - 4.1 Waltham, MA Apply Now Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $110,000 - $140,000 a year Qualifications Writing Skills Scrum Agile Application Development Computer Networking Full Job Description Who You'll Work With: Cloudlock was launched in 2011 with one simple goal in mind: to transform cloud security into a business enabler. From that initial goal, we\u2019ve built out a unified cloud security platform that helps organizations protect their sensitive data in public cloud applications such as Google\u2019s G Suite, Salesforce, Dropbox, Box, ServiceNow, and many others. After being acquired by Cisco in August 2016, Cloudlock now is part of the Cisco Cloud Security Business Unit, and remains a cohesive team that is headquartered in Waltham, Massachusetts, with remote offices in London and Israel. The cloud is our passion and cloud security is our mission. Cisco is one of the largest security companies in the world, with solutions ranging from Next-Generation Firewalls to Advanced Malware Protection and DNS-layer security. As part of Cisco, the opportunities here are endless as we continue to redefine cloud security. We're at the intersection of two very hot high-tech sectors, Cloud and Security. If you're as excited as we are about helping to shape the future of both, come join us! As a Sr. DevOps Engineer, you will directly contribute to the integrity, stability and success of our SaaS security solution. Come join our fun, dynamic team for this very cool opportunity. What You'll Do: Responsibilities: Tackle systems integration projects for monitoring, alerting, logging, scaling, and securing our cloud environments. Build and deploy immutable infrastructure and components. Assist with resolving systems-level problems encountered in production or during releases. Improve the DevOps feedback cycle by using production incidents to drive better automation, documentation, and monitoring that will reduce drag on staff efficiency. Support secure environment access by maintaining certificates, keys, and user and group security configuration. Provide high quality documentation and operations SOPs for new or existing system artifacts that can be used to share skills and facilitate better planning for our technical teams. Work as part of a highly skilled team using Agile methodologies to deliver and maintain high quality, efficient and scalable components and features. Keep up with industry best practices, trends, and standards on environment security, networking, automation, and maintenance tooling. Who You Are: At least 3 years of operations experience necessary, preferably with a SaaS product. At least 2 years of hands-on expertise with AWS, Terraform necessary. Substantial Python application development experience would be a big plus. Extensive experience with writing Bash scripts and Ansible playbooks necessary. Experience with Packer highly desirable Nice to have some PostgreSQL experience Very solid networking and security experience required, including routing, firewalls, DHCP, DNS, Route53, IP4 and IP6, VPN, SSH protocols and keys, tunnelling, SSL certificates. Hands-on experience required with some selection from Tenable Nessus, Trend Micro DSM, FreeRadius, Cisco ASAv, Splunk, Zabbix, Nagios, Librato, CollectD, StatsD, Grafana, AWS CloudWatch, AWS IAM, PostgreSQL, NGINX, Jenkins, RabbitMQ. Experience with large-scale infrastructure automation, particularly infrastructure-as-code approaches, desirable. At least 1 year of experience preferred with Agile approaches like Scrum, Kanban, or Lean. Experience with regulated or process-oriented work environments (e.g. FedRamp, SOC2, PCI, HIPAA, CMM, ISO 9001) would be a big plus. Why Cisco We connect everything: people, processes, data, and things. We innovate everywhere, taking bold risks to shape the technologies that give us smart cities, connected cars, and handheld hospitals. And we do it in style with unique personalities who aren't afraid to change the way the world works, lives, plays, and learns. Why Cisco Cloud Security Cisco Cloud Security enables you to securely adopt the cloud and better manage security for the way the world works today. It protects users against threats anywhere they access the internet and secures your data and applications in the cloud. You can also leverage the cloud to enhance security through simplified policy management and dynamic threat intelligence. With Cisco Cloud Security, you gain complete visibility into internet activity across cloud applications, all office locations, and roaming devices, plus faster threat detection and response. Cisco Cloud Security provides an effective security platform that is open, automated, and simple to use. And it\u2019s backed by industry-leading threat information delivered by the Cisco Talos security intelligence and research group. We Are Cisco! LI-JE1 dicedev #GD2015 ", 
